f=Engineering/aegis/custom/verified-patching/SKILL.md · in=verified-patching security finding actually closes: fix written, four independent checks pass **the fix builds, original proof-of-concept longer works, target's tests still pass, fresh adversary can't find way around it.** defending-code harness's patch-verification discipline (README stage made law, fourth check wired cypher's re-attack (when built) closure wired quinn's regression map. · p=patch stops specific PoC leaves vulnerability class open theater attacker adjusts input re-breaks it. patch fixes bug breaks test build new incident. four checks close four gaps: fix works, exploit dies, nothing regresses, *class* (not instance) closed. finding closed fragility mapped. · wu=Triggers: routed finding vuln-pipeline secure-code-review, "patch vulnerability," "verify security fix," "is finding closed," CVE remediation ops, any fix claiming close security finding. · st:/ Protocol=`A finding needs a fix (from vuln-pipeline / secure-code-review / ops CVE) \· -> Fix authored (by the owning builder; aegis coordinates, doesn't own their code) \· -> FOUR-CHECK VERIFICATION (all four, or NOT CLOSED): \· 1. BUILDS — the fix compiles/builds clean (per stack-profile build) \· 2. POC DIES — the original proof-of-concept no longer triggers the vulnerability` · in=**Four checks, partial credit.** finding closed four pass. "PoC dies" alone common false close fixes instance leaves class. Name which checks failed; finding stays open until four green. **PoC dies, verified finding lived.** execution-verified findings, re-run original PoC sandbox (Rail confirm longer triggers. static findings, demonstrate tainted path broken analysis, labeled static-confidence. **Tests pass, honestly.** existing suite stays green test weakened, skipped, deleted make fix pass (dev's integrity block §0, quinn's flaky rule). fix needs tests changed pass two changes; test change gets scrutiny. **Can't re-break class check.** fourth check what separates real fix theater: fresh adversarial attempt against vulnerability class different inputs, adjacent paths fail. cypher runs built (Rail in-scope, sandboxed); until aegis performs adversarial re-review, explicitly labeled self-check (weaker independent adversary, flagged rule 0.6). **aegis coordinates; owner authors; operator runs data changes.** aegis verifies fixes, doesn't builders' code owning agent writes fix, aegis runs four checks. Any fix mutates data prepared script operator executes (Rail 3), even security. **Closure feeds map.** closed finding becomes quinn regression-map entry class guarded fragile area, future recurrence caught gate. "closed" finding map entry isn't closed (quinn's no-guard-no-pass, security edition). · of=`## Patch Verification: [finding F-id] — [class] \· 1. Builds: ✓/✗ \· 2. PoC dies: ✓/✗ [sandbox re-run ref] \· 3. Tests pass: ✓/✗ [no tests weakened ✓] \· \· 4. Can't re-break: ✓/✗ [cypher ref / aegis self-check — labeled] \· Data change: [none / operator-run script ref (Rail 3)] \· ` · pr=**Four checks closed** fixing PoC without closing class theater., **PoC dies, verified sandbox** execution-verified findings lived (Rail 2)., **Tests stay green honestly** test weakened pass fix (integrity block)., **"Can't re-break" class check** adversary's fresh attempt fail; independent (cypher) beats self-check., **aegis verifies; owners author; operator runs data changes** (Rail 3)., **No closure without regression-map entry** class becomes guarded, isn't closed. · f=sandbox check (PoC dies) execution findings can't run finding cannot closed full confidence; static-confidence partial close, labeled, sandbox verification flagged pending., cypher built check aegis's adversarial re-review, explicitly labeled self-check weaker independent; finding's closure carries caveat until cypher re-attacks., Fix can't pass four (e.g., proper fix needs larger refactor) finding stays open; documented interim mitigation (WAF rule, feature flag, input cap) reduce severity, logged risk-accepted-with-mitigation operator, never closed., Author disputes failed check check's evidence stands; re-run confirm, red check waived argument. · b:with Other Skills=**vuln-pipeline secure-code-review** (siblings) produce findings closes; shared findings schema., **cypher** (adversary, built): runs check independently (Rail caged); re-attack failing what makes close trustworthy., **quinn/regression-map**: closure writes entry class becomes guarded fragile area; **quinn/test-strategy**: check quinn's suite., **dev/code-review-standards**: no-weakened-tests integrity rule shared; fixes still pass dev's normal review., **ops**: CVE fixes flow maintenance-hygiene; data-touching fixes ops-sequenced, operator-run (Rail 3).